Now BPP is healthy, but BIP is failing before pod creation.

The key line is:

ReplicaFailure   True    FailedCreate

and:

0/1 replicas created

This means Kubernetes cannot even create the pod object successfully.


---

Root Cause

Your BIP deployment is requesting too many SR-IOV resources.

Look carefully:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c:      2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_1:    2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2:    2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2_1:  2

That is:

2 VFs from bh0c

2 VFs from bh0c_1

2 VFs from bh0c_2

2 VFs from bh0c_2_1


Total = 8 SR-IOV VFs requested.


---

But Your Node Has

From your node allocatable:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c:      5
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_1:    5

But notice:

You did NOT show:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2_1

So those resources likely:

do not exist OR

are exhausted OR

SRIOV policy not created


Hence pod creation fails.


---

Confirm Exact Error

Run:

oc describe rs bscf5000-bip1-5c96c7bb87

OR:

oc get events --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp

You will likely see:

Insufficient openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0c_2

or similar.


---

Verify Existing SR-IOV Resources

Run:

oc describe node master.bscf5000.samsung.local | grep openshift.io/pci

Need full output.


---

Very Likely Issue

Your SR-IOV policies exist only for:

bh0c

bh0c_1

bh0u

bh0u_1

bh0u_2

bh0u_2_1


but NOT:

bh0c_2

bh0c_2_1



---

Verify SR-IOV Policies

Run:

oc get sriovnetworknodepolicy -A


---

Also Verify NADs

Run:

oc get network-attachment-definition -n cnf

You should see:

bscf-bh0c_2-nad

bscf-bh0c_2_1-nad


If missing → deployment references nonexistent resources.


---

Why BPP Works

BPP only requests:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2_1

which exist and are allocatable.

BIP requests additional VF pools that are unavailable.


---

Most Likely Final Fix

You need one of these:

Option 1

Create missing SR-IOV policies:

bh0c_2

bh0c_2_1


Option 2

Reduce VF count in Helm values

Option 3

Correct wrong NAD/resource names


